values:
Lately I've found myself questioning quite a bit of my life.&nbsp; I'm not sure if its introspection, or regrets of my past.&nbsp; I often feel like I'm going nowhere; conversely, I have a good job that I'm good at, a loving husband, and many reasons to be content.&nbsp; And yet, somehow, I feel...empty.&nbsp; I've noticed lately my depressive swings are somewhat more intense, but are somewhat shorter than they once were.&nbsp; I've also noticed lately an almost overwhelming craving for a cigarette; I&nbsp;quit 4 years ago.&nbsp; Somehow, I always want to smoke when I'm depressed.&nbsp; I usually want coffee at the same time, which is odd, but I think it came from my freshman year at college.&nbsp; I would leave for class about 30 minutes early, get a cup of coffee, a bagel, and have a cigigie between the Union and Blair Hall.&nbsp; I want a smoke when I have certain kinds of coffee, but I don't want coffee every time I&nbsp;have a cigarette. &nbsp;

I joined the Facebook-side of the force this week.&nbsp; I am finding people I remember from high school and college, yet I&nbsp;can't think of much to say to them.&nbsp; It's still nice to be connect though.

I think I&quot;m thinking too much and worrying too much.&nbsp; I'm going to go get some sleep (I hope) and dream of necromancers learning intriguing new methods of torture.&nbsp; Gee, I can't imagine why I'm such a bitch in the mornings....
